---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { MAILTO_AUDIT as mailto } from "../consts";
---

<Layout
  title="Component Debt: Design System Health Audits"
  description="A fixed-scope, fully async audit of your component library, tokens, theming, and accessibility. Written report, prioritized roadmap, and a recorded walkthrough in about one week."
>
  <header class="hero">
    <div class="gridmotif" id="gridmotif" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="page">
      <p class="kicker">Design System Health Audit</p>
      <h1>Find out what is <span class="hl">actually wrong</span> with your design system.</h1>
      <p class="sub">
        Your UI works, but it is quietly working against you. The audit turns
        vague friction into a specific, graded, evidence-backed plan. Fixed
        scope, fully async, about one week.
      </p>
      <div class="btnrow">
        <a class="cta" href={mailto}>Start an audit</a>
        <a class="cta secondary" href="#covers">See what it checks</a>
      </div>
      <p class="pricetag">
        <b>$2,500</b> fixed scope &nbsp;/&nbsp; about one week &nbsp;/&nbsp; fully
        async
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="ticker" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="track">
        <span>The same button built <b>six ways</b></span><span
          >Colors <b>hard-coded</b> instead of tokenized</span
        ><span>Spacing that ranges from <b>4px to 40px</b> at random</span><span
          >Primary button at <b>2.6:1</b> contrast</span
        ><span>No <b>theming layer</b></span><span
          >Components living in <b>someone's head</b></span
        >
        <span>The same button built <b>six ways</b></span><span
          >Colors <b>hard-coded</b> instead of tokenized</span
        ><span>Spacing that ranges from <b>4px to 40px</b> at random</span><span
          >Primary button at <b>2.6:1</b> contrast</span
        ><span>No <b>theming layer</b></span><span
          >Components living in <b>someone's head</b></span
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- CHECKS INTRO -->
  <section class="checks-intro" id="covers">
    <div class="page reveal">
      <p class="seclabel">What the audit checks</p>
      <h2 class="sectitle">
        Four things decide whether a system speeds a team up or taxes every
        change.
      </h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Each is graded against design-system maturity benchmarks. Everything
        below is live. These are the same problems the audit surfaces, shown
        the way the report shows them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CHECK 1: token architecture -->
  <section class="check">
    <div class="page reveal">
      <div class="copyc">
        <div class="pn" aria-hidden="true">01</div>
        <h3>One brand color, or three pretending to be one?</h3>
        <p>
          When color lives as literal hex across the code instead of a
          token, "the brand blue" drifts into several near-identical blues.
          Toggle to watch them resolve.
        </p>
        <span class="label-key">Token architecture</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stagebig">
        <div class="toggle" role="group" aria-label="Token view">
          <button type="button" data-tok="before" aria-pressed="true"
            >Found in code</button
          >
          <button type="button" data-tok="after" aria-pressed="false"
            >After tokenizing</button
          >
        </div>
        <div class="swatches" id="tokBefore">
          <div class="sw">
            <div class="chip" style="background:#2f6fed"></div>
            <div class="name">#2f6fed</div>
            <div class="subtle">card.css</div>
          </div>
          <div class="sw">
            <div class="chip" style="background:#2e6fed"></div>
            <div class="name">#2e6fed</div>
            <div class="subtle">nav.css</div>
          </div>
          <div class="sw">
            <div class="chip" style="background:#3170ee"></div>
            <div class="name">#3170ee</div>
            <div class="subtle">banner.css</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="swatches" id="tokAfter" hidden>
          <div class="sw" style="max-width:260px">
            <div class="chip" style="background:#2f6fed"></div>
            <div class="name">--color-brand</div>
            <div class="subtle">one source, referenced everywhere</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="driftnote" id="tokNote">
          <span class="icn" aria-hidden="true">!</span><span
            >Three "brand blues" that are meant to be one.</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="okline" id="tokOk" hidden>
          <span class="icn" aria-hidden="true">OK</span><span
            >One semantic token. A brand change is a one-line edit.</span
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CHECK 2: component API consistency -->
  <section class="check flip">
    <div class="page reveal">
      <div class="copyc">
        <div class="pn" aria-hidden="true">02</div>
        <h3>The same button, built six ways.</h3>
        <p>
          New work copies whichever button is nearest, so the count keeps
          growing. Each one carries its own padding, radius, hover, and
          disabled states to maintain.
        </p>
        <span class="label-key">Component API consistency</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stagebig">
        <div class="toggle" role="group" aria-label="Button view">
          <button type="button" data-btn="before" aria-pressed="true"
            >Found in code</button
          >
          <button type="button" data-btn="after" aria-pressed="false"
            >Canonical</button
          >
        </div>
        <div class="bbar" id="btnBefore">
          <span class="b b1">Save</span><span class="b b2">Save</span><span
            class="b b3">Save</span
          ><span class="b b4">Save</span><span class="b b5">Save</span><span
            class="b b6">Save</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="bbar" id="btnAfter" hidden>
          <span class="b bcanon">Save</span>
          <span class="mono btncaption"
            >one component, documented variants</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="caption mono" id="btnCap">
          6 implementations doing one job.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CHECK 3: accessibility -->
  <section class="check">
    <div class="page reveal">
      <div class="copyc">
        <div class="pn" aria-hidden="true">03</div>
        <h3>Contrast you can measure, not eyeball.</h3>
        <p>
          The most-clicked element in a product is often the one that fails.
          Contrast is computed against the AA floor of 4.5:1, and the verdict
          is shown by label, not color alone. Tab in to see real focus
          states.
        </p>
        <span class="label-key">Accessibility</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stagebig">
        <div class="cgrid">
          <div>
            <div class="csample cfail">
              <span class="lbl" aria-hidden="true">Primary action</span>
            </div>
            <span class="cverdict bad">FAIL 2.6:1</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="csample cpass">
              <span class="lbl" aria-hidden="true">Primary action</span>
            </div>
            <span class="cverdict good">PASS 4.6:1</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="caption mono">
          White text on #5b9bd5 vs. #2c6ca6. Same color family, one clears
          AA.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CHECK 4: documentation -->
  <section class="check flip">
    <div class="page reveal">
      <div class="copyc">
        <div class="pn" aria-hidden="true">04</div>
        <h3>Written down, or living in someone's head?</h3>
        <p>
          If a component is not specified, every engineer re-decides it. A
          system is documented when the contract is explicit and
          discoverable, not buried in source.
        </p>
        <span class="label-key">Documentation</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stagebig">
        <div class="spec">
          <div class="row"><span class="k">component</span><span>Button</span></div>
          <div class="row">
            <span class="k">variants</span><span
              >primary / secondary / ghost / destructive</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="row"><span class="k">sizes</span><span>sm / md / lg</span></div>
          <div class="row">
            <span class="k">tokens</span><span
              >--color-brand, --space-3, --radius-md</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="row">
            <span class="k">a11y</span><span
              >focus-visible ring, label required</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EVIDENCE -->
  <section class="evidence" id="evidence">
    <div class="page reveal">
      <p class="seclabel">What you get</p>
      <h2 class="sectitle">A graded report, the way a real one reads.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Every audit opens with a scorecard, then findings ordered by
        severity, each with where it lives, an example, a recommendation, and
        the impact of fixing it. From a sample engagement: fictional client,
        real format.
      </p>

      <div class="scoreband">
        <div class="score grade">
          <div class="n">C&minus;</div>
          <div class="l">Overall health</div>
        </div>
        <div class="score flag">
          <div class="n">10</div>
          <div class="l">Findings</div>
        </div>
        <div class="score flag">
          <div class="n">6</div>
          <div class="l">Button variants</div>
        </div>
        <div class="score flag">
          <div class="n">0</div>
          <div class="l">Shared token files</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="finding">
        <div class="fhead">
          <span class="id">DS-01</span><span class="sev crit">High</span>
        </div>
        <h3>No design tokens; color and spacing are hard-coded everywhere</h3>
        <div class="where">Found across 40+ component and stylesheet files</div>
        <p class="findingbody">
          Brand colors, spacing, and font sizes are written as literal
          values scattered through the codebase rather than referenced from
          a central source. The same blue appears as three different values,
          which is three "brand blues" that are meant to be one.
        </p>
        <pre class="code"><span class="c">/* card.css */</span>
.card-title &lbrace; color: #2f6fed; padding: 16px; &rbrace;
<span class="c">/* banner.css, same intent, different values */</span>
.banner h2  &lbrace; color: #3170ee; padding: 15px; &rbrace;</pre>
        <div class="impact">
          <strong>Impact:</strong> with a three-layer token system, a brand
          change becomes a one-line edit instead of a find-and-replace across
          the codebase, and theming becomes possible at all.
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="note muted">
        Severity is marked by shape (triangle, diamond, circle) and label as
        well as color, so it reads for everyone, including colorblind
        readers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OFFER -->
  <section class="offer-sec">
    <div class="page reveal">
      <p class="seclabel">The offer</p>
      <h2 class="sectitle">Fixed scope, fixed price. No hourly meter.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Start with the audit. It is the clear first step that tells you what
        to fix and in what order. Remediation is scoped against real
        findings, not guesses.
      </p>
      <div class="offer">
        <div class="tier featured">
          <span class="tag">Start here</span>
          <div class="name">Design System Health Audit</div>
          <div class="price">$2,500 <small>fixed / about one week</small></div>
          <ul class="clean">
            <li>
              Review of components, tokens, theming, and design-to-code
              consistency
            </li>
            <li>
              Accessibility (WCAG AA) gap check, contrast computed not
              guessed
            </li>
            <li>Written report with findings graded by severity</li>
            <li>Prioritized fix roadmap ordered by impact</li>
            <li>Recorded walkthrough you can watch on your own time</li>
            <li>One 30-minute Q&amp;A call included</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tier">
          <span class="tag">Next step</span>
          <div class="name">Remediation</div>
          <div class="price">
            $6k&ndash;$15k <small>scoped per project</small>
          </div>
          <ul class="clean">
            <li>Build the token layer (primitive, semantic, themed)</li>
            <li>Consolidate components into one documented library</li>
            <li>Theming foundation for dark mode or white-label</li>
            <li>Documentation and handoff so the team can maintain it</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DOGFOOD -->
  <section class="dogfood">
    <div class="page reveal">
      <p class="seclabel">Practicing what it checks</p>
      <h3>
        This page runs on the same kind of token system the audit looks for.
      </h3>
      <p>
        One type scale, one spacing scale, semantic color tokens, focus
        states on every interactive element, and severity that never depends
        on color alone. If a design-systems site cannot hold its own system
        together, why trust it with yours.
      </p>
      <div class="systable">
        <div>
          <h4>Type scale</h4>
          <div class="ramp">
            <span class="r40">Aa 40</span>
            <span class="r26">Aa 26</span>
            <span class="r16">Aa 16</span>
            <span class="r13">Aa 13</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Spacing scale</h4>
          <div class="scale-row"><i style="width:4px"></i> 4</div>
          <div class="scale-row"><i style="width:8px"></i> 8</div>
          <div class="scale-row"><i style="width:16px"></i> 16</div>
          <div class="scale-row"><i style="width:24px"></i> 24</div>
          <div class="scale-row"><i style="width:48px"></i> 48</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Color tokens</h4>
          <div class="tokrow">
            <span class="sw2" style="background:#5a2c66"></span> --accent2
          </div>
          <div class="tokrow">
            <span class="sw2" style="background:#3d1a45"></span> --accent
          </div>
          <div class="tokrow">
            <span class="sw2" style="background:#e8d5b0"></span> sand label
          </div>
          <div class="tokrow">
            <span class="sw2" style="background:#2a2622"></span> --body
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- START -->
  <section class="start" id="start">
    <div class="page reveal">
      <p class="seclabel centered">How to start</p>
      <h2 class="sectitle">
        Async by default. The only scheduled time is the closing Q&amp;A.
      </h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Send a note about your stack and what feels off. You will get a
        reply on fit and timing within two business days. If it is not a
        fit, you will hear that too.
      </p>
      <div class="btnrow centered">
        <a class="cta" href={mailto}>Email to start an audit</a>
        <a class="cta secondary" href={mailto} data-placeholder
          >Intake form (coming soon)</a
        >
      </div>
      <p class="note">
        The intake form points at email for now. It will be swapped for a
        hosted form once that is set up.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    function byId(id: string): HTMLElement {
      const el = document.getElementById(id);
      if (!el) throw new Error(`expected #${id} to exist`);
      return el;
    }

    (function () {
      // build hero grid motif
      const g = document.getElementById("gridmotif");
      if (g) {
        const cols = 16,
          rows = 7,
          total = cols * rows;
        for (let i = 0; i < total; i++) {
          const s = document.createElement("span");
          const r = Math.random();
          if (r > 0.93) {
            s.className = "sandlive";
            s.style.animationDelay = Math.random() * 7 + "s";
          } else if (r > 0.82) {
            s.className = "live";
            s.style.animationDelay = Math.random() * 6 + "s";
          }
          g.appendChild(s);
        }
        g.style.gridTemplateRows = "repeat(" + rows + ",1fr)";
      }

      function setPressed(group: ParentNode, active: Element) {
        group.querySelectorAll("button").forEach(function (b) {
          b.setAttribute("aria-pressed", b === active ? "true" : "false");
        });
      }

      document.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>("[data-tok]").forEach(
        function (btn) {
          btn.addEventListener("click", function () {
            const after = btn.dataset.tok === "after";
            if (btn.parentElement) setPressed(btn.parentElement, btn);
            (byId("tokBefore") as HTMLElement).hidden = after;
            (byId("tokAfter") as HTMLElement).hidden = !after;
            (byId("tokNote") as HTMLElement).hidden = after;
            (byId("tokOk") as HTMLElement).hidden = !after;
          });
        },
      );

      document.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>("[data-btn]").forEach(
        function (btn) {
          btn.addEventListener("click", function () {
            const after = btn.dataset.btn === "after";
            if (btn.parentElement) setPressed(btn.parentElement, btn);
            (byId("btnBefore") as HTMLElement).hidden = after;
            (byId("btnAfter") as HTMLElement).hidden = !after;
            byId("btnCap").textContent = after
              ? "One component, documented variants and sizes."
              : "6 implementations doing one job.";
          });
        },
      );

      // scroll reveal
      const io = new IntersectionObserver(
        function (entries) {
          entries.forEach(function (e) {
            if (e.isIntersecting) {
              e.target.classList.add("in");
              io.unobserve(e.target);
            }
          });
        },
        { threshold: 0.12 },
      );
      document.querySelectorAll(".reveal").forEach(function (el) {
        io.observe(el);
      });
    })();
  </script>

  <style>
    /* [hidden] loses the cascade to .swatches/.bbar's own display:flex
       (equal specificity, later rule wins), so toggled-off demo panels stay
       visible without this. */
    :global([hidden]) {
      display: none !important;
    }

    /* ---- Hero additions: headline highlight, button row, price line, grid motif, ticker ---- */
    .hero {
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      padding-bottom: 0;
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    .hero .page {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
      padding-top: 72px;
      padding-bottom: 72px;
    }
    .hero h1 .hl {
      color: #e8d5b0;
    }
    /* The global focus ring (--accent2, dark plum) fails AA on every dark
       band this page adds (hero, check rows, start): ~1.5:1, far under the
       3:1 UI floor. White matches the header's existing dark-bg override. */
    .hero a:focus-visible,
    .toggle button:focus-visible,
    .start a:focus-visible {
      outline-color: #fff;
    }
    .btnrow {
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .pricetag {
      margin-top: 24px;
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 13.5px;
      color: #e6ddd0;
    }
    .pricetag b {
      color: #fff;
    }

    .ticker {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .ticker .track {
      display: flex;
      gap: 48px;
      white-space: nowrap;
      padding: 14px 0;
      animation: scrollx 28s linear infinite;
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 13px;
      color: #cfc6b8;
    }
    .ticker .track span b {
      color: #e8d5b0;
    }
    @keyframes scrollx {
      from {
        transform: translateX(0);
      }
      to {
        transform: translateX(-50%);
      }
    }

    /* ---- Section scaffolding shared by checks-intro / evidence / offer / start ---- */
    .seclabel {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 12px;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin: 0 0 16px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
    }
    .seclabel::before {
      content: "";
      width: 30px;
      height: 2px;
      background: var(--accent);
    }
    .seclabel.centered {
      justify-content: center;
    }
    .sectitle {
      font-family: var(--display);
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: clamp(28px, 4.5vw, 44px);
      line-height: 1.08;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin: 0 0 20px;
      max-width: 20ch;
    }
    .lede {
      font-size: 18px;
      color: var(--body);
      max-width: 62ch;
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* ---- Checks intro: dark band so the demo rows have somewhere to sit ---- */
    .checks-intro {
      background: var(--grad-ink);
      padding: 72px 0 48px;
    }
    .checks-intro .sectitle {
      color: #fff;
    }
    .checks-intro .seclabel {
      color: #e8d5b0;
    }
    .checks-intro .seclabel::before {
      background: #e8d5b0;
    }
    .checks-intro .lede {
      color: #d6cdc0;
    }

    /* ---- Full-bleed alternating check rows (dark band continues) ---- */
    .check {
      background: var(--grad-ink);
      padding: 56px 0;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    }
    .check .page {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 48px;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .check.flip .copyc {
      order: 2;
    }
    .check .pn {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 44px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.42);
      line-height: 1;
      letter-spacing: -1px;
    }
    .check h3 {
      font-size: clamp(22px, 2.6vw, 30px);
      color: #fff;
      margin: 12px 0 12px;
      max-width: 18ch;
    }
    .check p {
      font-size: 16px;
      color: #d6cdc0;
      max-width: 46ch;
      margin: 0 0 16px;
    }
    .check .label-key {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #e8d5b0;
    }

    .stagebig {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.14);
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 32px;
    }
    .toggle {
      display: inline-flex;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.24);
      border-radius: 9px;
      overflow: hidden;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .toggle button {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 12.5px;
      border: 0;
      background: transparent;
      color: #d6cdc0;
      padding: 8px 15px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    .toggle button[aria-pressed="true"] {
      background: #e8d5b0;
      color: var(--grad-ink);
    }

    /* token swatches */
    .swatches {
      display: flex;
      gap: 16px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .sw {
      flex: 1;
      min-width: 110px;
    }
    .sw .chip {
      height: 76px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.18);
    }
    .sw .name {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 13px;
      color: #fff;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }
    .sw .subtle {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      color: #cfc6b8;
    }
    .driftnote,
    .okline {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 9px;
      font-size: 14px;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 11px 14px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    .driftnote {
      color: #ffd9d2;
      background: rgba(154, 43, 30, 0.24);
      border: 1px solid rgba(220, 120, 100, 0.5);
    }
